        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Typical usage of an image list follows the pattern below:</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Construct a <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>CImageList<ept id="p1">](../mfc/reference/cimagelist-class.md)</ept> object and call one of the overloads of its <bpt id="p2">[</bpt>Create<ept id="p2">](../mfc/reference/cimagelist-class.md#cimagelist__create)</ept> function to create an image list and attach it to the <ph id="ph1">`CImageList`</ph> object.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If you didn't add images when you created the image list, add images to the image list by calling the <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Add<ept id="p1">](../mfc/reference/cimagelist-class.md#cimagelist__add)</ept> or <bpt id="p2">[</bpt>Read<ept id="p2">](../mfc/reference/cimagelist-class.md#cimagelist__read)</ept> member function.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Associate the image list with a control by calling the appropriate member function of that control, or draw images from the image list yourself using the image list's <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Draw<ept id="p1">](../mfc/reference/cimagelist-class.md#cimagelist__draw)</ept> member function.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
